Using p = 0.05 as a threshold, there are potential nonlinear effects in the partial regression equation for the influence of Response Beliefs on Behavioral Intention. The same is potentially true for the effects of Distrusting Beliefs and Knowledge on Threat Beliefs, but as Threat Beliefs will be removed from the model because of a lack of effect, these potential effects will not be examined further.
Test alternate models with quadratic effects
To test for nonlinearity, one can model an interaction term of the exogenous construct with itself.
