For the alternate model, Knowledge is specified as a quadratic influence. Although the correct method would be two-stage, the model could only be estimated using the orthogonal and product-indicator method. Using this methods, the effect size is above the 0.02 threshold in both cases, and the t-statistic does indicate significance for the orthogonal method. This points to a potential quadratic effect of Knowledge on Response Beliefs. However, as this effect is still small, Knowledge will not be excluded in further model iteration.
Summary
Using the available tests, we found some evidence for a quadratic influence of Knowledge on Response Beliefs. We did not find evidence for a quadratic influence of any of the other exogenous variables.

