Hult, G. T. M., J. F. Hair, D. Proksch, M. Sarstedt, A. Pinkwart, & C. M. Ringle (2018). Addressing Endogeneity in International Marketing Applications of Partial Least Squares Structural Equation Modeling. Journal of International Marketing, 26(3), 1–21. https://doi.org/10.1509/jim.17.0151
Test of parametricity
The Gaussian Copula approach can only be used if the independent variable in question is not normally distributed. So we first test the distribution of the construct scores. A significant p value (p < 0.05) for either the Shapiro-Wilk or the Lilliefors test indicates that the data is not normally distributed.


