The Personal Moral Norm copula is significant in all model constellations (p < 0.1). However, adding the copula leads to a smaller path coefficient. Other than that, none of the copulas is significant in any of the model constellations, pointing to no endogeneity in the relationships between Behavioral Intention and its predictors.

